<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="388" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Barrett</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-19"><hi rend="italic">March 19,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 16.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 41, of the 13th ultimo, in regard to the additional duty of 8 cents
                            (making a total of approximately 21 per kilogram) imposed on foreign
                            flour.</p>
                        <p>It would appear that the figures given by you state the duty in Colombian
                            currency. If so, the equivalent in American gold might be stated for
                            greater convenience.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>